=head1 NAME

B<env2> - run a program in a modified environment

=head1 SYNOPSIS

#!PREFIX/env2 [-flags] <interpreter> [<interpreter_args>]

=head1 DESCRIPTION

B<env2> can serve as a replacement for env(1). It has many nice features.
The key feature is properly handling interpreter parameters on the #! line.
See the B<USE IN SHELL-SCRIPTS> section for details.
See the B<A BIT OF HISTORY> section for more on why this is necessary.

